div.p:
This field would be too large for me to travell over at this time, I ſhall therefore only thruſt my ſickle into one corner of it, and confine my diſcourſe unto that knowledge which God hath of men and their affairs, not only becauſe that will be moſt profitable, but alſo becauſe that ſeems to be the very reaſon why the Apoſtle mentions the Omniſcience of God in this place, that we might make application of it to our ſelves and our own actions, therefore he ſaith; 
